Here are some points:

You can add thousands of targeted affiliate products to any of your wordpress blog. This will help you [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/make-money/Make_Money-Profit_More_From_Your_Blog_With_BlogProfitz.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><em>This is a paid review of BlogProfitz</em></p>
<p>Scott Trimble has started a service called BlogProfitz to help people monetize their blogs better. This service can also be used as more value to your wordpress based blogs.</p>
<p>Here are some points:</p>
<ul>
<li>You can add thousands of targeted affiliate products to any of your wordpress blog. This will help you in fully monetizing their site quickly.</li>
<li>You can display targeted videos, articles (from our private database of 15k) and news to your blogs for more content and reader value. They have more than 15,000 private articles database.</li>
<li>the system is integrated with CommissionJunction, Clickbank, Affiliatebot, Amazon, eBay, YouTube, and many more other affiliate network. Its very easy to integrate them into the system. You just need to enter the affiliate ID for each one of them in their system and everything is done for you.</li>
<li>Its quite easy to use, anyone can jump in and get started. I just finish testing it myself.</li>
<li>You can use this service for any of your new or old wordpress based blogs.</li>
</ul>
<p>You can check the site <a href="http://blogprofitz.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_new">here</a>.</p>
<p>The system works in just 3 simple steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>After registering, just enter your affiliate codes for various affiliate nteworks.</li>
<li>Setup your new or existing blogs. Setting up is just entering the URL of your blog and its login/password.</li>
<li>And finally, setup the posting rules for the blog. These will dictate what kinds of affiliate products, articles, videos and news you pull into your blog.</li>
</ol>
<p>It is a very simple system to use. You can also checkout their <a  href="http://blogprofitz.com/tutorials.html" target="_new" rel="nofollow">tutorial videos</a>. Be sure to check out the last tutorial about posting videos, articles, and news.</p>
<p><center><a href="http://blogprofitz.com"><img src='http://www.jimkarter.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/blogprofitz-review.gif' alt='blogprofitz-review.gif' border='0' /></a></center></p>
]]></content:encoded>
