Its been more than a month since I am using Infolinks, instead of Kontera, on my sites. This post is the review of Infolinks services, providing information on how it is performing on my sites.
First, about the [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/make-money/Make_Money-Infolinks_Review.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Last month I wrote a small <a href="http://www.jimkarter.com/2009-03-15-infolinks-rocks-as-kontera-alternative.html" target="_new" rel="nofollow">post</a> about how I tried <a href="http://www.jimkarter.com/go/infolinks.php" target="_new">Infolinks</a> and then moved to it from Kontera.</p>
<p>Its been more than a month since I am using Infolinks, instead of Kontera, on my sites. This post is the review of Infolinks services, providing information on how it is performing on my sites.</p>
<p>First, about the integration of the code in the site. It was very simple, just put the code in the footer file of all my sites. That is it. No other changes required in the site.</p>
<p>About the earnings part, I am damn happy about it. In Kontera, I used to make around $8,000 to $9,000 per month. But with Infolinks, I have made more than $12,000 in a month. That is a big 50% increase in what I used to make with Kontera. So hands down to Infolinks in this regard.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.jimkarter.com/go/infolinks.php" target="_new" rel="nofollow"><img src='http://www.jimkarter.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/infolinks-review.png' alt='infolinks review' align="left" border="0" /></a>The earnings I am talking about are only from a subset of sites which I had with Kontera. I have still not moved 100% of my sites to Infolinks. I am moving them slowly. I think I will make even more when I move my other sites too. I am moving them slowly with time, so that I am able to track what sort of difference these new sites are making to my earnings.</p>
<p>I am sure when I will move most of my sites to Infolinks, it would be making me at-least $15,000 to $17,000 per month.</p>
<p>About the support part, I contacted their support team many times in last one month for adding my new sites. The response from the team was always within 24 hours. I really like a company if their support is prompt.</p>
<p>Overall, I would say <strong>Infolinks surely rocks</strong>. Thank god I moved.</p>
<p>If you still haven&#8217;t join them, <a href="http://www.jimkarter.com/go/infolinks.php" target="_new" rel="nofollow">go ahead and give them a try</a>. I am sure you will thank me for it. <img src='http://www.jimkarter.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /></p>
]]></content:encoded>
